This paper discusses the memorization and generalization capabilities of deep neural networks, which are central topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper analyzes how individual instances are treated by a model on the memorization-generalization continuum, which is a key aspect of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
